notes.note: Rec'd estimate from Silverzinc Motors for replacement of valve cover gasket and oil pan gasket (leaking). Called and spoke to customer, says she first noticed low oil light come on the screen about 2 months ago. Topped off the oil and the light went away. Had one oil change done previous to this light coming on the screen, no mention of any oil leaks by the garage at the time. Light came back on again, topped off oil and light went away. Asked garage she services with to keep an eye out for any leaks during the second service she did when she went in for brakes, and they found the valve cover gasket and oil pan gaskets leaking. Took it to Silverzinc for diag, then they submitted the claim. This leak is something that has progressed during the customer's ownership, not pre-exisiting. Moving forward with claim. M.P.
